e reports highlighted significant counterterrorism gains, including the rescue of 318 kidnapped victims, the disruption of oil theft valued at over ₦217 million and multiple successful military operations nationwide. The Nigerian Air Force also earned commendation for its strong showing at Nigeria’s first international airshow. [...] Zagazola\n\nSecurity Analysis, Counter Insurgency Expert. West Africa.\n\n##\n\nDetails\n:   Views : 7980\n\nCCC Report: DSS, Customs, NDLEA Lead Positive Media Coverage in December 2025\n\nThe Centre for Crisis Communication (CCC) has disclosed that the Department of State Security Service (DSS),\n\nNigeria Customs Service (NCS), and the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) dominated positive media coverage in December 2025, as Nigeria’s security, intelligence, military and emergency response agencies recorded strong national visibility driven by major operations, reforms and inter-agency collaboration. [...] According to the CCC’s December 2025 Media Review, an independent assessment of thousands of reports across traditional and online platforms, public perception of Nigeria’s Armed Forces, security and paramilitary institutions, intelligence agencies and emergency responders was largely positive. The review analysed coverage across four broad sectors—Armed Forces, Security/Paramilitary, Intelligence/Anti-Corruption, and Response Agencies—and found high levels of media engagement linked to operational successes, leadership initiatives and coordinated institutional actions.\n\n# Homeland Security Shutdown Sparks Travel Chaos And Political Clash\n\nFederal workers brace for unpaid shifts and travel delays as Congress stalls over immigration reforms after deadly Minnesota raids.\n\n6 min read\n\nAt the stroke of midnight on February 14, 2026, the U.S. Department of Homeland Security (DHS) officially ran out of funds, triggering a partial government shutdown that immediately rippled across the nation’s airports, disaster response operations, and border security apparatus. The shutdown, a result of an intense political standoff over immigration enforcement reforms, has left critical federal workers without pay and raised alarms about travel delays, disaster relief, and the broader state of American governance.\n\n### No headscarves in Kosovo\'s public school classrooms\n\nPoliticsJanuary 18, 202602:51 min\n\n### Pakistan\'s Pashtun kids struggle to go to school\n\nEducationJanuary 3, 202612:33 min\n\n### How insecurity is disrupting education in Nigeria\n\nSocietyDecember 10, 202503:50 min\n\n### What makes locs so controversial?\n\nSocietyDecember 8, 202509:22 min\n\n### How debt has reached record levels in Africa\n\nPoliticsNovember 20, 202503:52 min\n\n### Skating to school to cut costs in Nigeria\n\nCars and TransportationNovember 19, 202501:49 min\n\n### Women in Nigeria getting a second chance at an education\n\nEducationNovember 19, 202503:27 min\n\n### Ending learning poverty in Africa: Lessons from Ghana\n\nEducationNovember 13, 202502:27 min\n\n### How a board game is helping to clean up Kenya\'s streets [...] ScienceMarch 3, 202503:42 min\n\n### Norway\'s melting ice reveals artifacts hidden for centuries\n\nClimateOctober 22, 202404:39 min\n\nPage 1 of 24\n\nSkip next section Education\n\n## Education\n\n### Dance that defies borders: Ghana\'s cultural comeback\n\nDanceFebruary 13, 202605:31 min\n\n### Why are HIV infections rising in Poland?\n\nSocietyFebruary 12, 202604:41 min\n\n### India\'s elementary school helping students escape poverty\n\nEducationFebruary 11, 202602:02 min\n\n### Pakistan: Too young to earn, too poor to learn\n\nEducationFebruary 5, 202604:01 min\n\n### South Africa: Legitimate grievances or veiled xenophobia?\n\nEducationFebruary 1, 202604:12 min\n\n### How Africa nations are changing the future of learning\n\nEducationJanuary 24, 202601:40 min\n\n### No headscarves in Kosovo\'s public school classrooms [...] ### Gen Z leads Bulgaria\'s mass anti-corru